kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_req_fail (M1006C20)
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC connection request failures. When the message is tried to be decoded and the data is corrupted, the message cannot be interpreted (Unable to solve ASN.1 coding or the reason unknown). UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity is unable to solve the RRC connection request. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_reject (M1006C21)
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC Connection Request Reject messages. When the RRC signalling entity acknowledges the rejection to the UE. The reason for the rejection can be: - Internal reason - BTS reason - Transmission reason - AC reason. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a RRC_CONNECTION_REJECT message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_setup (M1006C22)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC:RRC CONNECTION SETUP messages sent by the RNC. This counter includes also repeated sendings of the message due to timer RRCconnRepTimer1 or RRCconnRepTimer2 expiry or due to a new RRC CONNECTION REQUEST from the UE. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends an RRC: RRC CONNECTION SETUP message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_setup_compl_sent (M1006C23)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE messages received. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE message from the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_rel (M1006C24)
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC connection releases. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends an RRC_CONNECTION_RELEASE message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: paging_type_1_att_cn_orig (M1006C25)
kpi_info.use: The number of CN originated paging type 1 attempts. Indicates the number of CN originated paging attempts to UEs in idle, Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state. UPDATED: When the RNC L2 entity has successfully scheduled PAGING TYPE 1 message for sending to the BTS and the paging procedure is triggered by the RANAP: PAGING message received from CN. Paging messages dropped due to overload are not included. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: paging_type_1_att_rnc_orig (M1006C26)
kpi_info.use: The number of RNC originated paging type 1 attempts. Indicates the number of RNC originated paging attempts to UEs in Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state. UPDATED:When the RNC L2 entity has successfully scheduled PAGING TYPE 1 message for sending to the BTS and the paging procedure is triggered by the RNC (e.g. after DL data received from PS-CN). Paging messages dropped due to overload are not included. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: paging_type_2_att (M1006C27)
kpi_info.use: A number of paging type 2 attempts. Indicates the number of (CN originated) paging attempts to mobiles in DCH or RACH/FACH substate. UPDATED:When the RNC sends a PAGING_TYPE_2 message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rb_setup (M1006C28)
kpi_info.use: A number of radio bearer setups. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a RADIO_BEARER_SETUP message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rb_setup_complete (M1006C29)
kpi_info.use: A number of radio bearer setups completed. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RADIO_BEARER_SETUP_COMPLETE message from the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rb_reconf (M1006C30)

kpi_info.title: rb_reconf_complete (M1006C31)

kpi_info.title: tran_ch_reconf (M1006C32)
kpi_info.use: "A number of transport channel reconfigurations. UPDATED: When the RRC signalling entity sends a TRANPORT_CHANNEL_RECONFIGURATION message to the UE." Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: tran_ch_reconf_comp (M1006C33)
kpi_info.use: A number of transport channel reconfigurations completed. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a TRANSPORT_CHANNEL_RECONFIGURATION_COMPLETE message from the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_due_cell_res (M1006C34)
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to a cell reselection. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Cell reselection'. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_per_update (M1006C35)
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to periodic update. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Periodic update'. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_data_transm (M1006C36)

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_r_link_fail (M1006C39)

kpi_info.title: cell_update_att_rlc_err (M1006C40)
kpi_info.use: A number of cell update attempts due to an RLC unrecoverable error. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a CELL_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'RLC unrecoverable error'. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ura_update_att_change_of_ura (M1006C41)
kpi_info.use: A number of URA update attempts due to a change of URA. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a URA_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Change of URA'. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ura_update_att_per_update (M1006C42)
kpi_info.use: A number of URA update attempts due to periodic update. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a URA_UPDATE message with CAUSE 'Periodic update'. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rrc_conn_mode_left_cell (M1006C43)
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC connected mode UEs that have moved to another cell. If an UE in CELL_DCH, CELL_FACH, CELL_PCH substate moves from the cell through SHO, HHO or CELL/URA update procedure. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity notices that the UE has moved to another cell. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: cap_req_ul (M1006C44)
kpi_info.use: The number of uplink capacity requests received from the UE. UPDATED: When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC: MEASUREMENT REPORT message with trafficVolumeEventResults IE from the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: cell_dch_state_to_cell_fach (M1006C45)
kpi_info.use: A number of state transitions from CELL_DCH state to CELL_FACH state. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RRC:RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC:RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE message and the dedicated channel release is triggered by a state transition attempt. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: cell_fach_state_to_cell_dch (M1006C46)
kpi_info.use: A number of state transitions from CELL_FACH state to CELL_DCH state. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC:RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC:TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message and the dedicated channel allocation is triggered by a state transition attempt. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: cell_fach_state_cell_pch_ina (M1006C47)
kpi_info.use: A number of state transitions from CELL_FACH state to CELL_PCH state after inactivity is detected. This counter is triggered when inactivity is detected in CELL_FACH. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC:PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE as a response to a state transition attempt.

kpi_info.title: cell_fach_state_cell_pch_upd (M1006C48)
kpi_info.use: A number of state transitions from CELL_FACH state to CELL_PCH state after Cell Update attempt. This counter is triggered: - When UE has moved temporarily to CELL_FACH due to cell change, re-entered service area or periodic cell update and after that returns to CELL_PCH state. - The counter shows also CELL_FACH state UEs moved directly to URA_PCH state (cell change frequency causes direct state change to URA_PCH) UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity switches the UE back to the CELL_PCH state by sending an RRC:CELL_UPDATE_CONFIRM message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: cell_fach_state_to_ura_pch (M1006C49)
kpi_info.use: The number of state transitions from CELL_FACH to URA_PCH state. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: mea_cap_req_for_dl (M1006C50)
kpi_info.use: The number of downlink capacity requests sent by the RNC MAC-C to the RRC signalling entity, triggering a state transition attempt to CELL_DCH state. UPDATED: When the RRC signalling entity receives a downlink capacity request from MAC-C. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: conn_cell_pch_due_ms_is_lost (M1006C51)
kpi_info.use: A number of RRC connection releases in CELL_PCH state due to a reason 'MS is lost'. If the RNC cannot obtain any cell update message as a response to repeated paging to the MS. If the timer which supervises periodical CELL update expires and MS has not made a periodical update before that. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity releases the RRC connection due to the reason 'MS is lost'. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rrc_con_rel_update_conf_fail (M1006C52)
kpi_info.use: This counter is not supported. UPDATED: Never. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rrc_con_rel_sig_con_re_est (M1006C53)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to the reason 'Directed signalling connection re-establishment'. This occurs when a UE in CELL_FACH, CELL_PCH or URA_PCH connected mode starts a CELL UPDATE/URA UPDATE procedure to a cell belonging to another RNC (than the SRNC) and relocation is not possible. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends an RRC_CONNECTION_RELEASE message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ini_dir_tran (M1006C54)
kpi_info.use: Number of Initial Direct Transfer messages UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a INITIAL_DIRECT_TRANSFER message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: sec_mod_contrl (M1006C55)

kpi_info.title: sig_conn_rel (M1006C57)

kpi_info.title: sig_conn_rel_ind (M1006C58)

kpi_info.title: phy_ch_reconf (M1006C59)

kpi_info.title: phy_ch_reconf_comp (M1006C60)

kpi_info.title: inter_rat_ho_utran (M1006C61)
kpi_info.use: Number of started Inter-RAT Hos for Packet Switched Calls. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends an RRC:CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: inter_rat_ho_utran_fail (M1006C62)
kpi_info.use: Number of failed Inter-RAT HOs for Packet Switched Calls. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC: CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message from the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ho_utran_com (M1006C63)
kpi_info.use: The number of sent Handover from UTRAN Commands for 2G or LTE inter-system handover. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity sends a RRC: HANDOVER FROM UTRAN COMMAND message to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ho_utran_com_fail (M1006C64)
kpi_info.use: The number of received Handover from UTRAN Command Failures for 2G or LTE inter-system handover. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a RRC: HANDOVER FROM UTRAN FAILURE message from the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: rrc_ho_utran_comp (M1006C65)
kpi_info.use: Number of received RRC handover to UTRAN complete messages for Circuit Switched Calls. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity receives a R RC:HANDOVER TO UTRAN COMPLETE message from the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_MODE_LEFT_CELL_UPD (M1006C66)
kpi_info.use: Number of RRC connected mode UEs that have moved to another cell through either CELL_UPDATE or URA_UPDATE procedure. UPDATED:When the RRC signalling entity notices that the UE has moved to another cell. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RB_RELEASE (M1006C67)
kpi_info.use: Number of Radio Bearer Release messages sent. UPDATED:When RRC:RADIO BEARER RELEASE message is sent to UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RB_RELEASE_COMPLETE (M1006C68)
kpi_info.use: Number of Radio Bearer Release complete messages received. UPDATED:When RRC:RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE message is received from UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_RMCU_OVERLOAD (M1006C69)
kpi_info.use: This counter is not supported. UPDATED:Never. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_DIR_SETUP (M1006C70)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Reject messages sent to the UE with RRC connection setup redirection information. In this case, the RRC connection request is rejected but the information of the other cell carrier is given where the UE should make a new connection request. The target cell can also be in the GSM network. UPDATED:When an RRC Connection Reject message is sent with redirection information. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: DCH_TO_FACH_PS_INTERRUPT_TIM (M1006C71)
kpi_info.use: The number of state transitions from CELL DCH to CELL FACH due to PS interruption timer. If PS Interruption Timer expires and there is another capacity request for the CELL that is under the same BTS, the packet scheduler of the RNC releases the dedicated transport channel and the related radio links. The UE is moved to Cell_FACH state unless it has other user plane dedicated transport channels allocated. UPDATED:When the UE is moved from Cell_DCH to Cell_FACH state due to PS Interruption Timer. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: PHY_CH_RECONF_FAIL (M1006C72)

Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RB_SETUP_FAIL (M1006C76)

kpi_info.title: SPARE_1_RRC (M1006C78)

kpi_info.title: CELL_DCH_FACH_LOW_UTIL (M1006C86)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC state transitions from CELL_DCH state to CELL_FACH or PCH state due to low DCH utilisation. If downlink or uplink throughput in the number of bytes goes below the threshold defined with the RNC configuration parameters DCHutilRelThrDL or DCHutilRelThrUL, the PS DCH release procedure starts. This counter can be updated both for Rel99 DCH/DCH and HSDPA. For HSDPA calls the counter is updated if the final trigger to initiate state transition was uplink low utilization. But if the final trigger was HS-DSCH downlink low utilization, the counter is not updated even if before that also uplink low utilization indication would have been received from L2. UPDATED: When the RRC signalling entity receives an RRC:RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message after DCH to FACH or DCH to PCH state transition due to low DCH utilisation.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_CELL_DCH (M1006C87)
kpi_info.use: The sum of operating time when the UE is in CELL_DCH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C89, gives the average operating time in CELL_DCH state. UPDATED:When the RRC state is changed from CELL_DCH state to another state, this counter is updated by the duration that the UE was in CELL_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_OPER_TIME_CELL_DCH (M1006C88)
kpi_info.use: The sum of squared operating time values when the UE is in CELL_DCH state. Needed for variance calculation. UPDATED:When the RRC state is changed from CELL_DCH state to another state, this counter is updated by the squared duration that the UE was in CELL_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_CELL_DCH (M1006C89)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counters M1006C87 and M1006C88. Needed for average and variance calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counters M1006C87 and M1006C88.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_CELL_FACH (M1006C90)
kpi_info.use: The sum of operating time when the UE is in CELL_FACH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C92, gives the average operating time in CELL_FACH state. The counter does not include those times that are used in CELL_FACH state when the UE is performing cell update or URA update procedure and after that is sent back to CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state, i.e. the UE is performing the periodic cell update or URA update procedure or cell or URA reselection. UPDATED:When the RRC state is changed from CELL_FACH state to another state, this counter is updated by the duration that the UE was in CELL_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_OPER_TIME_CELL_FACH (M1006C91)
kpi_info.use: The sum of squared operating time values when the UE is in CELL_FACH state. Needed for variance calculation. The counter does not include those times that are used in CELL_FACH state when the UE is performing cell update or URA update procedure and after that is sent back to CELL_PCH or URA_PCH state, i.e. the UE is performing periodic cell update or URA update procedure or cell or URA reselection. UPDATED:When the RRC state is changed from CELL_FACH state to another state, this counter is updated by the squared duration that the UE was in CELL_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_CELL_FACH (M1006C92)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counters M1006C90 and M1006C91. Needed for average and variance calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counters M1006C90 and M1006C91.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_CELL_PCH (M1006C93)
kpi_info.use: The sum of operating time when the UE is in CELL_PCH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C95, gives the average operating time in CELL_PCH state. Counting operating time in CELL_PCH is not interrupted if the UE performs cell update procedure due to periodic update or cell reselection. The unit of this counter is 10 seconds, meaning that value 1 means 10 seconds in CELL_PCH state. Times shorter than 10 seconds will be counted as 10 seconds. UPDATED:When the RRC state is changed from CELL_PCH state to another state (excluding cell updates), this counter is updated by the duration that the UE was in CELL_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_OPER_TIME_CELL_PCH (M1006C94)
kpi_info.use: The sum of squared operating time values when the UE is in CELL_PCH state. Needed for variance calculation. Counting operating time in CELL_PCH is not interrupted if the UE performs cell update procedure due to periodic update or cell reselection. UPDATED:When the RRC state is changed from CELL_PCH state to another state, this counter is updated by the squared duration that the UE was in CELL_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_CELL_PCH (M1006C95)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counters M1006C93 and M1006C94. Needed for average and variance calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counters M1006C93 and M1006C94.

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_URA_PCH (M1006C96)
kpi_info.use: Sum of operating time when UE is in URA_PCH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C98, gives the average operating time in URA_PCH state. Counting operating time in URA_PCH is not interrupted if UE performs cell update procedure due to periodic update or URA update. The unit of this counter is 10 seconds, meaning that value 1 means 10 seconds time in CELL-PCH state. Times shorter than 10 seconds will be counted as 10 seconds. UPDATED:When RRC state is changed from URA_PCH state to another state (excluding cell updates), this counter is updated by the duration that UE was in URA_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_OPER_TIME_URA_PCH (M1006C97)
kpi_info.use: This counter is not supported. UPDATED: This counter is never updated.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_URA_PCH (M1006C98)

kpi_info.title: ASSISTANCE_DATA_DELIVERY_MSG (M1006C99)
kpi_info.use: The number of sent UE positioning related Assistance Data Delivery messages. UPDATED:When an RRC:ASSISTANCE DATA DELIVERY message is sent to a UE.

kpi_info.title: RRC_SETUP_RETRANS_TRIG_BY_UE (M1006C100)

UPDATED:When an RRC:RRC CONNECTION REQUEST message is received from the UE before timer RRCconnRepTimer2 expires.

kpi_info.title: RRC_SETUP_RETRANS_TRIG_TIMER (M1006C101)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Setup retransmissions if RRC Connection Setup Complete is not received in the time defined in RRCconnRepTimer2. This counter does not include retransmissions due to timer RRCconnRepTimer1 expiry. UPDATED:When RRC Connection Setup retransmission is triggered by the expiration of RRCconnRepTimer2.

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_MSG (M1006C102)
kpi_info.use: The total number of received RRC STATUS messages with Protocol Error Information. UPDATED:When an RRC STATUS message is received with IE "Protocol error information" contents set to the value of the variable PROTOCOL_ERROR_INFORMATION.

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_INVALID_PAGING2 (M1006C103)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC STATUS messages received from the UE in cases where the UE receives a PAGING TYPE 2 message that contains a protocol error causing the variable PROTOCOL_ERROR_REJECT to be set to TRUE. UPDATED:When an RRC STATUS message is received with the IE "Received message type" value PAGING TYPE 2 and with the IE "Protocol error information" set to the value of the variable PROTOCOL_ERROR_INFORMATION.

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_INVALID_CONFIG (M1006C104)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC STATUS messages received from the UE in cases where radio access bearers for the CN domain indicated by the IE "CN domain identity" exist in the variable ESTABLISHED_RABS while a signaling connection release is requested by CN. UPDATED:When an RRC STATUS message is received with IE 'Received message type' value SIGNALLING CONNECTION RELEASE and IE 'Protocol error information' with value 'Message not compatible with receiver state'.

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_ASN1_VIOL_ENC_ERR (M1006C105)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC STATUS messages received from the UE in cases where the UE receives an RRC message on the DCCH for which the encoded message does not result in any valid abstract syntax value (or "encoding error"). UPDATED:When an RRC STATUS message is received with the IE "Protocol error information" containing IE "Protocol error cause" set to value "ASN.1 violation or encoding error".

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_ATT_DUE_NCCR (M1006C106)

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_SUCC_DUE_NCCR (M1006C107)

kpi_info.title: INTER_RAT_HO_UT_ATT_DUE_NCCR (M1006C108)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted Inter-RAT cell change orders from UTRAN due to blind Network Controlled Cell Reselection (NCCR) to GPRS due to service reason. UPDATED:When the RNC sends RRC:CELL CHANGE ORDER FROM UTRAN message to the UE.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REL_CCCH (M1006C109)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases on Common Control Channel. UPDATED:When the RRC:RRC CONNECTION RELEASE message is sent to the UE on CCCH.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_MSLOST_URA_PCH (M1006C110)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to 'MS is lost' in URA_PCH state. UPDATED:When a UE in URA_PCH state does not respond to paging or does not make a periodic URA update within URA_PCH supervision timer period and RNC releases the RRC Connection resources.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REL_RNC_INT (M1006C111)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to RNC internal reason. UPDATED:When RLC unrecoverable error happens in CELL_DCH or CELL_FACH state with PS connection.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_MSLOST_CELL_FACH (M1006C112)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases due to 'MS is lost' in CELL_FACH state. UPDATED:When the RRC connection is released due to the expiry of CELL_FACH state supervision timer.

kpi_info.title: CELL_DCH_HSDSCH_TO_FACH_LOW (M1006C113)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC state transitions from CELL DCH (HS-DSCH) state to CELL FACH state due to low utilisation, low throughput or inactivity. M1006C86 is updated along with this counter if the final trigger to initiate state transition was Rel99 uplink low utilization. UPDATED: When CELL_DCH (HS-DSCH) to CELL_FACH state transition occurs due to any other reason than radio interface failure.

kpi_info.title: CELL_DCH_STATE_TO_CELL_PCH (M1006C114)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC state transitions from CELL_DCH state to CELL_PCH state. UPDATED:The counter is updated when the UE is transferred from the CELL_DCH state to CELL_PCH state (after releasing of the CS-service or due to the inactivity detection of PS-RB(s)). The RRC entity switches the UE directly from CELL_DCH to CELL/URA_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: CELL_DCH_HSDSCH_TO_CELL_PCH (M1006C115)

UPDATED: The counter is updated in case of HSPDA if the state transition occurs directly from CELL_DCH to CELL_PCH. kpi_info.title: DCH_REL_DUE_RES_TIMER (M1006C116)

kpi_info.title: DCH_REL_DUE_RES_TIMER_REJECT (M1006C117)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when HSDPA resumption timer has expired but reconfiguration to DCH 0/0 is rejected. The reason for rejection can be one of the following: 1) The maximum number of HSDPA users is exceeded in the cell. 2) It is not possible to allocate HSDPA power to the cell. 3) There is another parallel layer-3 procedure ongoing. 4) HdschGuardTimerHO or HsdschGuardTimerLowThroughput timer is running. UPDATED:When HSDPA resumption timer expires but layer 3 telecom entity or admission control rejects reconfiguration to DCH 0/0.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_SUCC_NRT (M1006C118)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful RRC connection re-establishments. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after an RRC connection re-establishment procedure has been completed. This applies when the UE has at least one NRT RAB in use or only Signalling Radio Bearer.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_UE_NRT (M1006C119)

UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message from the UE after an attempted RRC connection re-establishment procedure. This applies when the UE has at least one NRT RAB in use or only Signalling Radio Bearer.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_NOREPLY_NRT (M1006C120)

UPDATED:When the UE does not send a reply to the RNC for the RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message that the RNC sends during an RRC-connection re-establishment procedure. This applies when the UE has at least one NRT RAB in use or only Signalling Radio Bearer.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_ADD_ATT (M1006C121)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted radio link additions with an active set update procedure. UPDATED:When an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE message is sent by the serving RNC to the UE for adding one or more radio links to the active set. The counter is updated by the number of radio links that are attempted to be added to the active set, also in a cell replacement procedure. The counter is updated for the cells that are attempted to be added to the active set. In case of a DRNC cell, the WBTS-0/WCEL-0 object is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_ADD_SUCC (M1006C122)

UPDATED:When the serving RNC receives an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message from the UE, this counter is updated by the number of radio links added with the active set update procedure, also in a cell replacement procedure. The counter is updated for the cells which were added to the active set. In case of a DRNC cell, the WBTS-0/WCEL-0 object is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_ADD_FAIL_UE (M1006C123)

The counter is updated for the cells which were attempted to be added to the active set. In case of a DRNC cell, the WBTS-0/WCEL-0 object is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_ADD_NOREPLY (M1006C124)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed radio link additions with an active set update procedure due to the UE not responding to an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE message. UPDATED:When the serving RNC does not receive a reply to an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE message sent to the UE, this counter is updated by the number of radio links that were attempted to be added into the UE's active set with the active set update procedure, also in a cell replacement procedure. The counter is updated for the cells which were attempted to be added into the active set. In case of a DRNC cell, the WBTS-0/WCEL-0 object is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_DEL_ATT (M1006C125)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted radio link deletions with an active set update procedure. UPDATED:When an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE message is sent by the serving RNC to the UE for deleting one or more radio links to the active set. The counter is updated by the number of radio links that are attempted to be deleted from the active set, also in a cell replacement procedure. The counter is updated for the cells that are attempted to be deleted from the active set. In case of a DRNC cell, the WBTS-0/WCEL-0 object is used.

kpi_info.title: AS_UPDATE_RL_DEL_SUCC (M1006C126)

The counter is updated for the cells which were deleted from the active set. In case of a DRNC cell, the WBTS-0/WCEL-0 object is used.

kpi_info.title: ATT_RB_SETUP_HSDPA (M1006C149)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted Radio Bearer setups for HSDPA. UPDATED:When the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION to the UE with information to configure the radio bearer to use HS-DSCH, and the radio bearer was not using HSDPA previously. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_RB_SETUP_HSDPA (M1006C150)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Radio Bearer setups for HSDPA. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE after a successful configuration of Radio Bearer to use HS-DSCH, and the radio bearer was not using HSDPA previously. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ATT_FACH_TO_HS_DSCH (M1006C151)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from FACH to HS-DSCH. UPDATED:When the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE with the condition that channel switches from FACH to HS-DSCH. Both HS-DSCH/DCH and HS-DSCH/E-DCH are included. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_FACH_TO_HS_DSCH (M1006C152)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from FACH to HS-DSCH. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful channel switch from FACH to HS-DSCH. Both HS-DSCH/DCH and HS-DSCH/E-DCH are included. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HS_DSCH_TO_FACH (M1006C153)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from HS-DSCH to FACH. UPDATED:When the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message to the UE with the condition that the channel switches from HS-DSCH to FACH. Both HS-DSCH/DCH and HS-DSCH/E-DCH are included. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_HS_DSCH_TO_FACH (M1006C154)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from HS-DSCH to FACH. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful channel switch from HS-DSCH to FACH. Both HS-DSCH/DCH and HS-DSCH/E-DCH are included. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: PAGING_OCCASION_CELL_PCH (M1006C155)
kpi_info.use: The number of occasions when paging is required for UE in Cell-PCH state, i.e. the RNC starts paging. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell-PCH state and RANAP: PAGING is received or downlink data transfer is needed. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: PAGING_MESSAGES_CELL_PCH (M1006C156)
kpi_info.use: The number of paging messages sent to UE in Cell-PCH state. This counter contains all sent pages, not only repeated ones, before the UE response is received or before paging is stopped due to no response from the UE. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell-PCH state and the RNC sends RRC: PAGING TYPE 1 message. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPD_AFTER_PAG_CELL_PCH (M1006C157)
kpi_info.use: The number of Cell updates counted as a paging response received from the UE after paging in Cell-PCH state. This counter is also used as a denominator when average paging delay is calculated from M1006C163. UPDATED: When message RRC: CELL UPDATE is received after paging from a UE in Cell-PCH state: 'Paging response', 'Cell reselection', 'Periodic update', 'Data transmission' and 'Re-entering service area'. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_PAG_NO_RESP_CELL_PCH (M1006C158)
kpi_info.use: The number of unsuccessful paging occasions when the RNC judges the whole paging occasion unsuccessful due to no response from the UE. UPDATED:In case of UTRAN paging, after the whole UTRAN originated paging occasion is executed (including UTRAN originated paging repetitions). The RRC entity sets 2 second timer to wait for a paging response from the UE. If the 2 second timer expires, the counter is increased by one. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: PAGING_OCCASION_URA_PCH (M1006C159)
kpi_info.use: The number of occasions when paging is required for UE in URA-PCH state, i.e. the RNC starts paging. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE responds to paging, or if the UE does not respond the counter is updated for the cell that is the last known location of the UE. UPDATED:When the UE is in URA-PCH state and RANAP: PAGING is received or downlink data transfer is needed. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: PAGING_MESSAGES_URA_PCH (M1006C160)
kpi_info.use: The number of paging messages sent to UE in URA-PCH state. This counter contains all sent pages, not only repeated ones, before the UE response is received or before paging is stopped due to no response from the UE. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE responds to paging, or if the UE does not respond the counter is updated for the cell that is the last known location of the UE. UPDATED:When the UE is in URA-PCH state and the RNC sends RRC: PAGING TYPE 1 message. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPD_AFTER_PAG_URA_PCH (M1006C161)
kpi_info.use: The number of Cell updates counted as a paging response received from the UE after paging in URA-PCH state. This counter is also used as a denominator when average paging delay is calculated using M1006C166. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE responds to paging. UPDATED:When message RRC: CELL UPDATE is received after paging from a UE in URA-PCH state: 'Paging response', 'Cell reselection', 'Periodic update', 'Data transmission' and 'Re-entering service area'. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_PAG_NO_RESP_URA_PCH (M1006C162)
kpi_info.use: The number of unsuccessful paging occasion when the RNC judges the whole paging occasion unsuccessful due to no response from the UE. The counter is updated for the cell that was the last known location of the UE. UPDATED: In case of UTRAN paging, after the whole UTRAN originated paging occasion is executed (including UTRAN originated paging repetitions). The RRC entity sets 2 second timer to wait for a paging response from the UE. If the 2 second timer expires, the counter is increased by one. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: PAG_DELAY_CU_CELL_PCH (M1006C163)
kpi_info.use: The sum of Cell-PCH paging delays defined as the time between the first sent RRC: PAGING TYPE 1 message and the RRC: CELL UPDATE received from the UE. This counter, divided by M1006C157, provides the average paging delay. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE after paging. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: PAG_DELAY_RESP_CELL_PCH (M1006C164)
kpi_info.use: The sum of Cell-PCH paging delays defined as the time between the first sent RRC: PAGING TYPE 1 message and the RRC: UTRAN MOBILITY INFORMATION CONFIRM or any other UL DCCH message received from the UE after a successful connection establishment procedure. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C165 provides the average paging delay. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE responds to paging. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: UTRAN MOBILITY INFORMATION CONFIRM or any other UL DCCH received from the UE after a successful connection establishment procedure. The counter is not updated if the timer waiting for UE response expires. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_PAG_DELAY_RESP_CEL_PCH (M1006C165)
kpi_info.use: The number of paging delay values updated to counter M1006C164. Used as a denominator in average calculation. UPDATED:Updated by value 1 when the paging delay value is updated to counter M1006C164. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SUM_PAG_DELAY_CU_URA_PCH (M1006C166)

kpi_info.title: DENOM_PAG_DELAY_RESP_URA_PCH (M1006C168)
kpi_info.use: The number of paging delay values updated to counter M1006C167. Used as a denominator in average calculation. UPDATED:Updated by value 1 when the paging delay value is updated to counter M1006C167. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: PRACH_DELAY_RANGE_VALUE (M1006C169)
kpi_info.use: The value of WCEL parameter PRACHDelayRange when the last RRC Connection Request or Cell Update of the measurement interval was received. UPDATED:When the last RRC Connection Request or Cell Update of the measurement interval was received.

kpi_info.title: SUM_ST_TRANS_TIME_PCH_FACH (M1006C170)
kpi_info.use: Sum of state transition times from Cell-PCH or URA-PCH state to Cell-FACH state, defined as the time between: RRC: Cell Update (cause: UL Data Transmission or Paging response) - RRC: positive UL-DCCH ack as a response to Cell Update Confirm. This counter, divided by the denominator, provides the average state transition time. When the UE is/was in PCH state with RNTIs allocated and transfers itself to HS-FACH state by sending ('dummy') RRC: Measurement Report, the counter is updated by value zero because the state transition is completed immediately when the RNC receives the Measurement Report. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: positive UL-DCCH ack as a response to Cell Update Confirm. When the UE was in PCH state with RNTIs allocated, the trigger for counter update is the reception of ('dummy') RRC: Measurement Report. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_ST_TRANS_TIME_PCH_FACH (M1006C171)
kpi_info.use: Denominator for M1006C170 used for average calculation.UPDATED: Updated by value 1, then the measured time is updated to counter M1006C170. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.
