kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_UE_RT (M1006C187)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed RRC connection re-establishments due to the UE replying with a new RRC: CELL UPDATE message, for UEs with at least one RT RAB. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message from the UE after an attempted RRC connection re-establishment procedure and the UE has got at least one RT RAB. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_NOREPLY_RT (M1006C188)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed RRC connection re-establishments due to the UE not replying to an RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message sent by the RNC, for UEs with at least one RT RAB. UPDATED:When the RNC does not receive a reply to RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message initiated by the RRC connection re-establishment procedure and the UE has got at least one RT RAB. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_SUCC_MR (M1006C189)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful RRC connection re-establishments for UEs with at least two RABs. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after an RRC connection re-establishment procedure and the UE has got at least two RABs. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_UE_MR (M1006C190)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed RRC connection re-establishments due to the UE replying with a new RRC: CELL UPDATE message, for UEs with at least two RABs. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message from the UE after an attempted RRC connection re-establishment procedure and the UE has got at least two RABs. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_NOREPLY_MR (M1006C191)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed RRC connection re-establishments due to the UE not replying to an RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message sent by the RNC, for UEs with at least two RABs. UPDATED:When the RNC does not receive a reply to RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message initiated by the RRC connection re-establishment procedure and the UE has got at least two RABs. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_SETUP_HSDPA_NOREPLY (M1006C192)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups for HSDPA due to UE not responding. UPDATED:When the UE does not respond to the RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION message sent by the RNC and a timer expires in the RNC or the UE makes a Cell Update. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_SETUP_HSDPA_UE (M1006C193)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups for HSDPA due to UE responding with a failure message. UPDATED:When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SUM_TIME_AAL2_SETUP (M1006C194)
kpi_info.use: Sum of Iub AAL2 Setup time, defined as the difference between ALCAP: Establishment Request (ERQ) and ALCAP: Establishment Confirm (ECF). This counter, divided by the denominator, provides the average AAL2 setup time. UPDATED: When the RNC receives ALCAP: Establishment Confirm (ECF). Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_TIME_AAL2_SETUP (M1006C195)
kpi_info.use: Denominator for M1006C194, used for average calculation. UPDATED: Updated by value 1, then the measured time is updated to counter M1006C194. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ATT_PCH_DCH_TRANS_UMRLC (M1006C196)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted Cell/URA-PCH to DCH state transitions using UM-RLC. This counter is updated for the cell where RRC: CELL UPDATE was originally received, even if the UE would be redirected to another cell. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC:CELL UPDATE CONFIRM including Cell/URA-PCH to DCH state transition command to the UE. This counter is updated once per ongoing state transition procedure, not for each L3 retransmission of RRC:CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_PCH_DCH_TRANS_UMRLC (M1006C197)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Cell/URA-PCH to DCH state transition attempts using UM-RLC. This counter is updated for the cell where RRC: CELL UPDATE was originally received, even if the UE would be redirected to another cell. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC:RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE after a successful state transition directly from Cell/URA-PCH to DCH. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: RESEL_PCH_DCH_TRANS (M1006C198)
kpi_info.use: The number of cell reselections that occurred during the attempted Cell/URA-PCH to DCH state transitions using UM-RLC. This counter can be used in the Cell Update success rate calculation for excluding the reselections from the attempts. This counter is updated for the cell where RRC: CELL UPDATE was originally received, even if the UE would be redirected to another cell. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC:CELL UPDATE message from another cell than the current serving cell after sending the RRC:CELL UPDATE CONFIRM including Cell/URA-PCH to DCH state transition command to the UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_ATT_DATA_TR_TVM (M1006C199)
kpi_info.use: The number of Cell Update messages received with cause "uplink data transmission" and "traffic volume indicator" IE set as true. Also M1006C36 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message with cause "uplink data transmission" and "traffic volume indicator" set as true. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: INACT_HSPA_REL_DUE_PREV_OVER (M1006C200)
kpi_info.use: The number of inactive HSPA user plane releases due to preventive overload control. UPDATED:When an RRC signalling entity receives an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message after successful HSPA user plane release to Cell-FACH or DCH 0/0 due to preventive overload control

kpi_info.title: CAP_REQ_REL_HSPA_DUE_PRE_OVE (M1006C201)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when UL or DL capacity request is received for a user within 10 seconds of user plane release due to preventive overload control. UPDATED:When either UL or DL capacity request is received for a radio bearer whose HSPA user plane has been released within previous 10 seconds due to preventive overload control.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIGURED_FLEXIBLE_RLC (M1006C202)
kpi_info.use: The number of radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use Flexible-RLC. UPDATED:When the UE replies with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating a successful configuration of Flexible-RLC and Flexible RLC was not in use before the reconfiguration. This counter is updated separately for each RAB using Flexible-RLC DL.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_IUB_OVERLOAD (M1006C203)
kpi_info.use: "The number of RRC connection rejections due to Iub overload control. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC CONNECTION REJECT message to the UE because NBAP operations are restricted due to window-based self adjusting Iub overload control, C-NBAP overload or overload indication received from the BTS. Also M1006C21 is updated along with this counter."

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_MAX_REGIST (M1006C204)
kpi_info.use: "The number of RRC connection rejections due to maximum amount of registrations and inter-RAT cell reselections per ICSU. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC CONNECTION REJECT message to the UE due to attempting registration or inter-RAT cell reselection, and the maximum number of such procedures per ICSU has been exceeded. Also M1006C21 is updated along with this counter."

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_CENT_UNIT_OVERL (M1006C205)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection rejections due to centralized signaling unit RSMU overload. This counter is supported only in IPA-RNC but not in mcRNC. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC CONNECTION REJECT message to the UE because RSMU unit is overloaded. Also M1006C21 is updated along with this counter.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_BUF_LIMIT_CTRL (M1006C206)
kpi_info.use: "The number of RRC connection rejections due to buffer limit control. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC CONNECTION REJECT message to the UE because the number of unhandled messages in a signalling unit has exceeded a specified threshold value. Also M1006C21 and M1001C618 are updated along with this counter."

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_CN_FAIL (M1006C207)
kpi_info.use: This counter is currently not supported. UPDATED: This counter is currently not supported.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REJ_RNC_RESTART (M1006C208)
kpi_info.use: "The number of RRC connection rejections due to RNC recovery after restart. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC CONNECTION REJECT message to the UE because the RNC has recently restarted and the maximum number of RRC connection establishments is limited until a guard timer expires. Also M1006C21 is updated along with this counter."

kpi_info.title: ATT_RB_SETUP_DCHSDPA (M1006C209)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DC-HSDPA. Includes initial DC-HSDPA allocations, reconfigurations from SC-HSDPA to DC-HSDPA, hard handovers and serving cell changes. Also M1006C149 is updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION to the UE with information to configure the radio bearer to use DC-HSDPA

kpi_info.title: SUCC_RB_SETUP_DCHSDPA (M1006C210)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DC-HSDPA. Includes initial DC-HSDPA allocations, reconfigurations from SC-HSDPA to DC-HSDPA, hard handovers and serving cell changes. Also M1006C150 is updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE after a successful configuration of Radio Bearer to use DC-HSDPA.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_SETUP_DCHSDPA_NOREP (M1006C211)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DC-HSDPA due to UE not responding. Also M1006C192 is updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond to the RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message sent by the RNC for DC-HSDPA establishment and a timer expires in the RNC.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_SETUP_DCHSDPA_UE (M1006C212)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DC-HSDPA due to UE responding with a failure message. Also M1006C193 is updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE for DC-HSDPA establishment attempt.

kpi_info.title: ATT_RB_SETUP_BLIND_HO (M1006C234)
kpi_info.use: The number of blind handover attempts to another frequency using Radio Bearer Setup or Physical Channel Reconfiguration method. If the blind handover is performed using the Radio Bearer Setup, counter M1006C28 is updated along with this counter. If the blind handover is performed using the Physical Channel Reconfiguration, counter M1006C59 is updated. UPDATED: This counter is updated either when the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP to the UE with the command to setup Radio Bearer on another frequency, or when the RNC sends RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION to the UE as triggered by RAB assignment procedure. This counter is updated for the main cell of the connection during blind handover attempt (source cell of the blind HO).

kpi_info.title: SUCC_RB_SETUP_BLIND_HO (M1006C235)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful blind handovers to another frequency using Radio Bearer Setup or Physical Channel Reconfiguration method. If the blind handover is performed using the Radio Bearer Setup, counter M1006C29 is updated along with this counter. If the blind handover is performed using the Physical Channel Reconfiguration, counter M1006C60 is updated. UPDATED: If the frequency layer change is performed using the Radio Bearer Setup procedure, this counter is updated when RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE is received from the UE. If the blind handover is performed using the Physical Channel Reconfiguration method, this counter is updated when the RNC receives RRC: PYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE before sending Radio Bearer Setup. This counter is updated for the target cell of the blind HO.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_BLHO_UENACK_WO_MEAS (M1006C236)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed blind handovers to another frequency due to negative response from the UE when handover was done without monitored cell RSCP/EcNo measurement result. If the blind handover was performed using the Radio Bearer Setup, M1006C76 is updated along with this counter. If the blind handover was performed using the Physical Channel Reconfiguration, counter M1006C72 is updated. UPDATED: When negative acknowledgement is received from the UE after an attempt to establish Radio Bearer on another frequency, and the attempt was done to a cell configured by the parameter ADJI-BlindHOTargetCell, without inter-frequency RSCP or EcNO measurement result received from the UE. If the blind handover is performed using the Radio Bearer Setup method, the trigger message is RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE. If the blind handover is performed by Physical Channel Reconfiguration method, the trigger message is RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE. This counter is updated for the main cell of the connection during blind handover attempt (source cell of the blind HO).

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_BLHO_UENACK_W_MEAS (M1006C237)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed blind handovers to another frequency due to negative response from the UE when handover was done to a cell indicated by target cell RSCP/EcNo measurement result. If the blind handover was performed using Radio Bearer Setup, M1006C76 is updated along with this counter. If the blind handover was performed using Physical Channel Reconfiguration, counter M1006C72 is updated. UPDATED: When negative acknowledgement is received from the UE after an attempt to establish Radio Bearer on another frequency, and the attempt was done to a cell indicated by the UE inter-frequency RSCP or EcNo measurement result. If the blind handover is performed using Radio Bearer Setup method, the trigger message is RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE. If the blind handover is performed by Physical Channel Reconfiguration method, the trigger message is RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE. The counter is updated for the main cell of the connection during blind handover attempt (source cell of the blind HO).

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_BLHO_UELOST_WO_MEAS (M1006C238)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed blind handovers to another frequency due to lost UE when handover is done without monitored cell RSCP/EcNo measurement result. UPDATED: This counter is updated when: the UE does not respond to the blind handover command sent by the RNC, the timer expires in the RNC, and the attempt was done to a cell configured by the parameter ADJI-BlindHOTargetCell, without inter-frequency RSCP or EcNo measurement result received from the UE. This counter is also updated if the UE responds with RRC: CELL UPDATE. If the blind handover is performed using Physical Channel Reconfiguration method, the handover command is RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION. If the blind handover is performed using Radio Bearer Setup method, the handover command is RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP. The counter is updated for the main cell of the connection during blind handover attempt (source cell of the blind HO).

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_BLHO_UELOST_W_MEAS (M1006C239)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed blind handovers to another frequency due to lost UE when handover is done to a cell indicated by target cell RSCP/EcNo measurement result. UPDATED:This counter is updated when: the UE does not respond to the blind handover command sent by the RNC, the timer expires in the RNC, and the attempt was done to a cell indicated by the UE inter-frequency RSCP or EcNo measurement result. This counter is also updated if the UE responds with RRC: CELL UPDATE. If the blind handover is performed using Physical Channel Reconfiguration method, the handover command is RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION. If the blind handover is performed using Radio Bearer Setup method, the handover command is RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP. The counter is updated for the main cell of the connection during blind handover attempt (source cell of the blind HO).

kpi_info.title: SUM_OPER_TIME_EFACH (M1006C213)
kpi_info.use: The sum of operating time when the UE is in Enhanced Cell_FACH state. This counter, divided by the denominator M1006C214, gives the average operating time in Enhanced Cell_FACH state. The counter does not include those times that are used in Enhanced Cell_FACH state when the UE ia performing cell update or URA update procedure and after that is sent back to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state, i.e., the UE is performing the periodic cell update or URA update procedure or cell or URA reselection. UPDATED: When the RRC state is changed from Enhanced Cell_FACH state to another state, this counter is updated by the duration that the UE was in Enhanced Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: NUM_UE_MEAS_EFACH (M1006C214)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counter M1006C213. Needed for average calculation. UPDATED: When the duration value is updated to counter M1006C213, this counter is updated by value 1.

kpi_info.title: ATT_DCH_TO_EFACH (M1006C215)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_DCH (HSxPA or Rel99) to Enhanced Cell_FACH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the RNC sends reconfiguration message to the EFACH capable UE with condition that the channel switches from Cell_DCH state to Cell_FACH state (using HSPA transport channels).

kpi_info.title: SUCC_DCH_TO_EFACH (M1006C216)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Cell_DCH (HSxPA or Rel99) to Enhanced Cell_FACH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the RNC receives reconfiguration acknowledgement message from the EFACH capable UE after a successful state transition from Cell_DCH state to Cell_FACH state (using HSPA transport channels).

kpi_info.title: ATT_EFACH_TO_DCH (M1006C217)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Enhanced Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (on HSxPA or Rel99). The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When a UL capacity request (RRC signalling entity initiated) or a DL capacity request (MAC-D entity initiated) is sent to RRM and the UE is in EFACH state.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_EFACH_TO_DCH (M1006C218)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Enhanced Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (on HSxPA or Rel99). The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the RNC receives reconfiguration acknowledgement message from the EFACH capable UE after a successful state transition from EFACH state to Cell_DCH state (on HSxPA or Rel99)

kpi_info.title: ATT_PCH_TO_EFACH (M1006C219)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_PCH to Enhanced Cell_FACH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED:When a dummy measurement report or Cell Update is received from the UE and RRM in the RNC is asked to change state for EFACH capable UE from Cell_PCH state to Cell_FACH (using HSPA transport channels).

kpi_info.title: SUCC_PCH_TO_EFACH (M1006C220)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Cell_PCH to Enhanced Cell_FACH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED:If the state transition was triggered by Cell Update message, the counter is updated when the RNC receives reconfiguration acknowledgement message from the EFACH capable UE after a successful state transition from Cell_PCH state to Cell_FACH state (using HSPA transport channels). If the state transition was triggered by RRC Measurement Report received from the UE, there is not any further RRC signaling with the UE (but 'local' transition to HS-Cell_FACH). In this case the counter is updated along with M1006C219.

kpi_info.title: ATT_EFACH_TO_PCH (M1006C221)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Enhanced Cell_FACH to Cell_PCH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED:When the RNC sends reconfiguration message to the EFACH capable UE with condition that the channel switches from Cell_FACH state (on HSPA) to Cell_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_EFACH_TO_PCH (M1006C222)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Enhanced Cell_FACH to Cell_PCH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED:When the RNC receives reconfiguration acknowledgement message from the EFACH capable UE after a successful state transition from Cell_FACH state (on HSPA) to Cell_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: CELL_FACH_TO_IDLE (M1006C223)
kpi_info.use: The number of state transitions from Cell_FACH to IDLE state. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_FACH state and the RNC connection is released for any reason, either normally or due to some failure. Cell_FACH relocation or directed signalling connection re-establishment to another RNC shall not update this counter.

kpi_info.title: ATT_FACH_TO_DCH (M1006C224)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (any transport channel). The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP message to the UE for transferring the UE to Cell_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_DCH_TO_FACH (M1006C225)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_DCH (any transport channel) to Cell_FACH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_DCH state and the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message to transfer the UE to Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_FACH_TO_PCH (M1006C226)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_FACH to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message for transferring the UE to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state. This does not include cases when the UE in Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state makes Cell Update or URA Update and only temporarily visits in Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_PCH_TO_FACH (M1006C227)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_PCH or URA_PCH to Cell_FACH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state and the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message from the UE triggering transfer to Cell_FACH. The counter is not be updated if the Cell Update or URA Update triggers RRC connection release or going back to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_DCH_TO_PCH (M1006C228)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_DCH (any transport channel) to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH. The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_DCH state and state transition to Cell_PCH or URA_PCH is attempted with RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION.

kpi_info.title: ATT_PCH_TO_DCH (M1006C229)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_PCH or URA_PCH to Cell_DCH (any transport channel). The counter is updated on RRC-connection level, not separately for each RAB. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_PCH or URA_PCH state and the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message from the UE triggering direct transfer to Cell_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: ATT_FACH_TO_HS_DSCH_EDCH (M1006C230)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (HS-DSCH/E-DCH). The counter is updated separately for each RAB for which the state transition happens. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION or RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message for transferring the UE to Cell_DCH state with HS-DSCH/E-DCH transport channel.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HS_DSCH_EDCH_TO_FACH (M1006C231)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted state transitions from Cell_DCH (HS-DSCH/E-DCH) to Cell_FACH. The counter is updated separately for each RAB for which the state transition happens. UPDATED: When the UE is in Cell_DCH state with HS-DSCH/E-DCH transport channel and the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE, or RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM message for transferring the UE to Cell_FACH state.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_FACH_TO_HS_DSCH_EDCH (M1006C232)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful state transitions from Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (HS-DSCH/E-DCH). The counter is updated separately for each RAB for which the state transition happens. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message after a successful state transition from Cell_FACH to Cell_DCH (HS-DSCH/E-DCH).

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_FLEXIBLE_RLC_UL (M1006C233)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use Flexible-RLC in uplink direction. M1006C202 can be updated in parallel with this counter because it indicates the Flexible-RLC usage in the downlink direction. UPDATED: When the UE replies with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating a successful configuration of Flexible-RLC in uplink direction that was not in use before the reconfiguration. This counter is updated separately for each RAB using Flexible-RLC UL.

kpi_info.title: ATT_INT_BTS_PCH_FACH_TO_DCH (M1006C240)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted inter-BTS layer changes in PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transition. UPDATED: When the UE is in URA_PCH/Cell_PCH/Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: CELL UPDATE CONFIRM or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION to the UE, attempting to move the UE into Cell_DCH state under another BTS. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_INT_BTS_PCH_FACH_TO_DCH (M1006C241)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful inter-BTS layer changes in PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transition. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating a successful inter-BTS layer change during transition to Cell_DCH state. The counter is updated for the target cell where the UE was successfully redirected.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_INT_BTS_PCH_FACH_TO_DCH (M1006C242)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed inter-BTS layer changes in PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transition. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE but responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: CELL UPDATE or does not respond at all and a timer expires in the RNC. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt.

kpi_info.title: SIG_CONN_REL_IND_PS_END (M1006C243)
kpi_info.use: "The number of RRC: Signalling Connection Release Indication messages received from the UE with cause ""UE Requested PS Data session end"". Also M1006C58 is updated along with this counter. M1006C58 includes all Signalling Connection Release Indications with or without the cause IE. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: Signalling Connection Release Indication message from the UE, with value ""UE Requested PS Data session end"" in IE ""Signalling Connection Release Indication Cause""."

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_MIMO_SUCC (M1006C245)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use MIMO. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating successful MIMO allocation and MIMO was not active before the procedure.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_MIMO_FAIL (M1006C246)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use MIMO. UPDATED: When the UE responds with negative RRC acknowledgement message, Cell Update or does not respond at all when trying to configure MIMO to use.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_64QAM_SUCC (M1006C247)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use 64QAM. When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating successful 64QAM allocation and 64QAM was not active before the procedure.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_64QAM_FAIL (M1006C248)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use 64QAM. UPDATED: When the UE responds with negative RRC acknowledgement message, Cell Update or does not respond at all when trying to configure 64QAM to use.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_HSFACH_DL (M1006C249)
kpi_info.use: "The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use HS-FACH downlink. UPDATED: When the RNC receives positive RRC protocol acknowledgement from the UE after configuring it to use HS-FACH downlink and HS-FACH was not in use before that.The counter is not updated in HS-RACH to HS-FACH reconfiguration."

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_HSFACH_UL (M1006C250)
kpi_info.use: "The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use HS-FACH uplink (HS-RACH). UPDATED: When the RNC receives positive RRC protocol acknowledgement from the UE after configuring it to use HS-FACH uplink and HS-FACH uplink was not in use before that.The counter is updated also in HS-FACH (only DL) to HS-RACH (also UL) reconfiguration."

kpi_info.title: PAGING_DROP_LOW_PRIORITY (M1006C251)
kpi_info.use: The number of low priority paging records that were dropped in L2 scheduling. UPDATED: When the L2 entity of RNC drops low priority paging message because of congestion.

kpi_info.title: PAGING_DROP_HIGH_PRIORITY (M1006C252)
kpi_info.use: The number of high priority paging records that were dropped in L2 scheduling. UPDATED: When the L2 entity of RNC drops high priority paging message because of congestion.

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_ATT_CS_CALL (M1006C253)
kpi_info.use: "The number of started Cell Update procedures with establishment cause ""Originating Conversational Call"", ""Terminating Conversational Call"" or ""Emergency Call"".""Establishment cause"" is an optional IE in the Cell Update message introduced by 3GPP Rel5.Also one of basic Cell Update counters M1006C34-M1006C40 is updated along with this counter depending on the ""Cell update cause"" IE used by the UE.UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: CELL UPDATE message with cause ""Originating Conversational Call"", ""Terminating Conversational Call"" or ""Emergency Call""."

kpi_info.title: CELL_UPDATE_SUCC_CS_CALL (M1006C254)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Cell Update procedures with establishment cause "Originating Conversational Call", "Terminating Conversational Call" or "Emergency Call". "Establishment cause" is an optional IE in the Cell Update message introduced by 3GPP Rel5. Also one of basic Cell Update counters M1006C34-M1006C40 is updated along with this counter depending on the "Cell update cause" IE used by the UE. UPDATED: When the UE responds with Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete or UTRAN Mobility Information Confirm after the RNC has sent Cell Update Confirm as a response to Cell Update with the mentioned causes.

kpi_info.title: UE_ID_LFDPHONE_STATE_TR (M1006C255)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection sessions in which a UE has been identified as a Rel5 Legacy Fast Dormancy phone (LFDphone) based on the 'Signalling Connection Release Indication (SCRI) without cause' from the UE. This UE is able to easily send SCRIwithoutCause in the future and by RAN2451 feature, RNC tries to avoid idle state and uses Cell_PCH instead. This means that for RRC connection sessions during which: - RNC has identified UE as a Rel5-iPhone and after every SCRIwithoutCause, RNC will move UE to Cell_PCH instead of idle or - RNC has identified UE as a Rel5-non-iPhone (which IMSI had been stored after previous SCRI for some time) and during this session, the RNC uses Smart timers in order to avoid idle state. UPDATED: When the RNC identifies UE as an LFDphone (only once per RRC connection session), - based on the 1st SCRIwithoutCause (Rel5-iPhone) or - based on the temporarily stored IMSI (Rel5-non-iPhone)

kpi_info.title: LFDPHONE_TO_PCH (M1006C256)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when a Rel5 Legacy Fast Dormancy phone (LFDphone) has made a successful transition to Cell/URA_PCH state. This means that for cases (after SCRIwithoutCause during the current or the previous session) when: - RNC moves Rel5-iPhone to Cell_PCH immediately after SCRIwithoutCause and later moves it again due to SCRI or due to RNC timer (NOTE: iPhone still uses normal inactivity timers). - RNC moves Rel5-non-iPhone to Cell_PCH before SCRIwithoutCause (after using Smart timers in this session due to stored IMSI after SCRIwithoutCause in the previous session). Also, other state transition counters (for example M1006C47, M1006C49 or M1006C114) are updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC receives a positive RRC protocol acknowledgement message from Rel5 LFDphone (see M1006C255), indicating a successful transition to Cell/URA_PCH state.

kpi_info.title: LFDPHONE_PCH_TO_FACH_DCH (M1006C257)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when a Rel5 Legacy Fast Dormancy phone (LFDphone) has made a successful transition from Cell/URA_PCH state to Cell_FACH/DCH/HSPA. This means that for cases (after earlier SCRIwithoutCause during the current or the previous session) when: - Rel5-iPhone returns from PCH and RNC moves it to Cell_FACH/DCH/HSPA. - Rel5-non-iPhone returns from PCH and RNC moves it to Cell_FACH/DCH/HSPA and continues to use Smart timers. Also, other state transition counters (for example M1006C171) are updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC receives a positive RRC protocol acknowledgement message from Rel5 LFDphone (see M1006C255), indicating a successful transition from Cell/URA_PCH state to Cell_FACH/DCH/HSPA.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_HIGH_PEAK_REDIR_MCRNC (M1006C258)
kpi_info.use: This counter is not supported. UPDATED: Never.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_LOW_PEAK_REDIR_MCRNC (M1006C259)
kpi_info.use: This counter is not supported. UPDATED: Never.

kpi_info.title: HIGH_PEAK_UE_TO_IPARNC (M1006C260)
kpi_info.use: This counter is not supported. UPDATED: Never.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_REDIR_MCRNC (M1006C261)
kpi_info.use: This counter is not supported. UPDATED: Never.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_LTE_REDIR_INACT (M1006C262)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Releases triggered by Smart LTE Layering feature because of inactivity or PS RAB release. Also M1006C24 is updated along with this counter. This counter is applicable also in case of 'RAN2980 Measurement Based LTE Layering'. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE, triggered by Smart LTE Layering feature because of Cell_DCH to Cell_FACH/Cell_PCH/URA_PCH transition or PS RAB release. The counter is updated only once per RRC Connection Release procedure, not counting repeated messages sent by the RNC. The object of the counter update is the main cell of the connection that may be different than the cell based on which the layering decision was done.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_LTE_REDIR_CH_SWI (M1006C263)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Releases triggered by Smart LTE Layering feature because of switch from HSPA to Rel99 DCH transport channels. Also M1006C24 is updated along with this counter. This counter is applicable also in case of 'RAN2980 Measurement Based LTE Layering'. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE, triggered by Smart LTE Layering feature because of HS-DSCH to Rel99 DCH (DCH x/y) channel type switch. HS-DSCH switches directly to Rel99 DCH without any bit rate (DCH 0/0) are not included in this counter. The counter is be updated only once per RRC Connection Release procedure, not counting repeated messages sent by the RNC. The object of the counter update is the main cell of the connection that may be different than the cell based on which the layering decision was done.

kpi_info.title: LTE_REDIR_PREV_TIMER (M1006C264)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when Smart LTE Layering is prevented by timer RNMOBI->SmartLTELayeringPrevT. High value in this counter may indicate insufficient coverage of the target LTE layer, or incorrect neighbour cell definition. UPDATED: When Smart LTE Layering would trigger RRC Connection Release, but it is prevented by timer RNMOBI->SmartLTELayeringPreventionT. The counter is updated only once during the RRC connection lifetime, even if the Smart LTE Layering algorithm would be evaluated many times and preventing the layering execution. The object of the counter update is the main cell of the connection that may be different than the cell based on which the layering decision was done.

kpi_info.title: ATT_INTRA_BTS_TR_TO_DCH (M1006C265)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted intra-BTS inter-frequency PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transitions with MBLB enabled. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt. UPDATED: When the UE is in URA_PCH/Cell_PCH/Cell_FACH state and the RNC sends RRC: Cell Update Confirm or RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration to the UE, attempting to move the UE into Cell_DCH state under the same BTS but different frequency and MBLB functionality is enabled.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_INTRA_BTS_TR_TO_DCH (M1006C266)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful intra-BTS PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH state transitions where frequency layer was changed because of MBLB. The counter is updated for the target cell where the UE was successfully redirected. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete indicating a successful intra-BTS inter-frequency layer change during transition to Cell_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_INTRA_BTS_TR_TO_DCH (M1006C267)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed intra-BTS frequency layer changes in PCH/FACH to Cell_DCH transition with MBLB enabled. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond with RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete, sends RRC: Cell Update to the original frequency or a timer waiting for UE response expires in the RNC, after a frequency layer change was attempted.

kpi_info.title: CANC_INTRA_BTS_TR_TO_DCH (M1006C268)
kpi_info.use: The number of intra-BTS frequency layer changes in PCH to Cell_DCH transition cancelled because of CPICH RSCP quality check. The counter is updated for the cell where the UE was located before the state transition attempt. UPDATED: When inter-frequency PCH to Cell_DCH is cancelled because of CPICH RSCP value sent by the UE in RRC: Cell Update does not fulfill the quality check criteria.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_WCDMA_REDIR (M1006C269)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Releases with redirection information to another WCDMA frequency. Also M1006C24 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE including redirection information to another WCDMA frequency. The counter is be updated only once per RRC Connection Release procedure, not counting repeated messages sent by the RNC.

kpi_info.title: CS_CALL_TERM_RE_EST (M1006C270)
kpi_info.use: The number of CS voice calls terminated during RRC connection re-establishment procedure. This counter can be used to analyze the cases where the user terminates the call because it becomes mute for a while during re-establishment, and thus the user experiences a drop even if the call could recover soon after that. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND or RANAP: RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST requesting to release CS RAB while the RNC is waiting for RRC connection re-establishment to happen.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_LTE_REDIR_CS_REL (M1006C291)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC Connection Releases with LTE redirection information because of CS Voice Call release. Also M1006C24 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE, triggered by LTE redirection because of CS voice call release when the UE has at least one active PS RAB. The counter is be updated only once per RRC Connection Release procedure, not counting repeated messages sent by the RNC. The object of the counter update is the main cell of the connection that may be different than the cell based on which the layering decision was done.

kpi_info.title: ATT_RB_SETUP_DBHSDPA (M1006C293)
kpi_info.use: The number of attempted Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DB-HSDPA. Includes initial DB-HSDPA allocations, reconfigurations from SC-HSDPA to DB-HSDPA, hard handovers and serving cell changes. M1006C209 is also updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using DC-HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the RNC sends RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION to the UE with information to configure the radio bearer to use DB-HSDPA.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_RB_SETUP_DBHSDPA (M1006C294)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DB-HSDPA. It includes initial DB-HSDPA allocations, reconfigurations from SC-HSDPA to DB-HSDPA, hard handovers and serving cell changes. M1006C210 is also updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using DC-HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE after a successful configuration of Radio Bearer to use DB-HSDPA.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_SETUP_DBHSDPA_NOREP (M1006C295)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DB-HSDPA because of UE not responding. Also M1006C211 is updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using DC-HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the UE does not respond to the RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION message sent by the RNC for DB-HSDPA establishment and a timer expires in the RNC.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_RB_SETUP_DBHSDPA_UE (M1006C296)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed Radio Bearer setups/reconfigurations for DB-HSDPA because of UE responding with a failure message. Also M1006C212 is updated along with this counter if the radio bearer was not using DC-HSDPA previously. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION FAILURE for DB-HSDPA establishment attempt.

kpi_info.title: DCH_STATE_ALLOC_PTT_SUCC (M1006C297)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful PTT call attempts in the cell. UPDATED:When PTT RAB is successfully transitioned to CELL_DCH state.

kpi_info.title: DCH_STATE_ALLOC_PTT_FAIL (M1006C298)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed PTT call attempts in the cell. UPDATED:When CELL_DCH state allocation for PTT RAB is not possible due to RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration failure/ a second RRC: Cell update message is received from the UE in same cell/ no response from PTT UE to RRC: Radio Bearer Reconfiguration.

kpi_info.title: ACT_OPER_TM_PTT_UE (M1006C299)
kpi_info.use: Sum of PTT UE operating time in active state. This counter divided by the denominator M1006C300 gives the average time that PTT RAB is in active state with user plane allocated. UPDATED:When PTT RAB leaves active state, duration for which PTT RAB was active(time between Radio Bearer Reconfiguration Complete to PTT dormancy timer expiry) is updated to this counter

kpi_info.title: DENOM_ACT_OPER_TM_PTT_UE (M1006C300)
kpi_info.use: The number of samples for active state operating time counter M1006C299. UPDATED:Incremented by one every time SUM OF PTT UE ACTIVE STATE OPERATING TIMES is updated

kpi_info.title: MEH_INCR_TVM_PEND_TIME (M1006C301)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the RNC configures the increased Traffic Volume Measurement pending time for the UE because of The Mass Event Handler functionality setting the cell in "load" state, that being the direct result of NRT scheduling queue length exceeding the threshold defined by WCEL-MEHQueueThreshold and WCEL-MEHLoadStateTtT. This number includes also cases when the increased Traffic Volume Measurement pending time was used because of temporary HSDPA user amount restriction due to Voice Call Priorization During High Traffic Load. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the RNC sends RRC: MEASUREMENT CONTROL to the UE with an increased Traffic Volume Pending Time.

kpi_info.title: MEH_INCR_CQI_CYCLE (M1006C302)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocations where increased CQI feedback cycle is configured for the UE by Mass Event Handler functionality because the amount of HSDPA users in the cell has reached the threshold defined by WCEL-MEHHSDPAUserNbrCQI. This Mass Event Handler action can occur also without M1000C406 and M1000C407. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the first HS-DSCH flow is allocated for the UE in a cell. This can be initial allocation during RRC connection setup, RAB setup if SRB is not already on HSPA, state transition to Cell_DCH, user plane setup from DCH 0/0, serving cell change, channel type switch or HHO.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_DC_HSUPA_SUCC (M1006C303)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use DC-HSUPA. UPDATED: When the UE replies with for example RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE indicating a successful configuration of DC-HSUPA that was not in use before the reconfiguration.

kpi_info.title: RB_CONFIG_DC_HSUPA_FAIL (M1006C304)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed radio bearer setups and reconfigurations to use DC-HSUPA. UPDATED: When the RNC is not able to successfully configure the UE to use DC-HSUPA, due to no response from the UE or the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE or RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE.

kpi_info.title: RRC_CONN_REDIR_GSM_FAIL (M1006C305)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when a UE redirected to GSM comes back to the RNC within 20 seconds of redirection. This can be interpreted to imply that the UE was not able to connect to the GSM network. UPDATED:When a UE redirected to GSM with RRC Connection Reject sends new RRC Connection Request to the RNC within 20 seconds of redirection.

kpi_info.title: SUCC_PCH_DCH_DATA_SESS_PROF (M1006C309)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful Cell/URA-PCH to DCH state transitions triggered by Data Session Profiling. This means state transitions where the UE did not set "Traffic volume indicator" flag in the Cell Update message, but the RNC still chooses Cell_DCH as the target state based on the previous data transfer activity of the UE. Also the generic PCH to DCH state transition counters are updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC:RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC:PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE from the UE after a successful state transition from Cell/URA-PCH to DCH and the state transition was triggered by Data Session Profiling feature.

kpi_info.title: RRC_REL_LTE_REDIR_DCH (M1006C310)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection releases for LTE redirection due to periodic trigger.UPDATED:When the RNC sends RRC Connection Release message to the UE redirecting it to LTE, and the redirection was performed due to periodic trigger. The counter is be updated only once per RRC Connection Release procedure, not counting repeated messages sent by the RNC.

kpi_info.title: CS_CALL_RADIO_CONN_LOST (M1006C311)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when a CS call loses radio connection and is dropped out of Cell_DCH state. After this the call may still be re-established if T314>0, but this counter is indicating that the user may experience some break in voice. The counter is updated for the main cell of the connection at the moment of losing the radio connection.UPDATED:When a UE with at least one CS RAB loses radio connection so that the call is dropped out of Cell_DCH into state waiting for re-establishment (when T314>0) or CS RAB release is triggered (when T314=0).

kpi_info.title: FAIL_HSUPA_IFHO_CM_UE (M1006C312)
kpi_info.use: The number of UE rejections for compressed mode activation when compressed mode for measuring 3G carrier is attempted while the UE is on HSUPA transport channel. UPDATED:When negative RRC protocol acknowledgement is received from the UE as a response for compressed mode activation.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_LTE_CM_UE (M1006C313)
kpi_info.use: The number of UE rejections for activating compressed mode for LTE carrier measurement. The counter is updated regardless of what is the used transport channel during compressed mode measurement. UPDATED:When negative RRC protocol acknowledgement is received from the UE as a response for compressed mode activation.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_SUCC_RT_IUR (M1006C314)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful RRC connection re-establishments for UEs with at least one RT RAB when the RRC connection re-establishment happens over the Iur interface. The counter is updated in the target cell of re-establishment. M1006C186 is also updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE, RRC: RADIO BEARER RELEASE COMPLETE, RRC: PHYSICAL CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC: TRANSPORT CHANNEL RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE after an RRC connection re-establishment procedure over Iur interface and the UE has got at least one RT RAB.

kpi_info.title: RRC_RE_EST_FAIL_RT_IUR (M1006C315)
kpi_info.use: The number of RRC connection re-establishment failures over Iur for UEs with at least one RT RAB. The counter is updated in the target cell of re-establishment.UPDATED:When RRC connection re-establishment over Iur fails either in the resource allocation phase or the UE is not able to re-establish Cell_DCH state connection.

kpi_info.title: AMR_122_74_59_475_UE_FAIL (M1006C316)
kpi_info.use: The number AMR codec mode set {12.2, 7.4, 5.9, 4.75} setups or reconfigurations failed due to UE. UPDATED: When the RNC receives negative RRC protocol response from the UE, or the UE does not respond at all, when trying to setup or reconfigure AMR codec mode set {12.2, 7.4, 5.9, 4.75} into use.
